william hume  lydall  inc  zoominfocom jaquelin h hume  wikipedia jaquelin h hume from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search jaquelin h hume born  harbor point michigan died october   san francisco california cause of death cancerrelated stroke residence san francisco california education princeton university harvard business school occupation businessman philanthropist political party republican party spouses caroline howard hume children patricia highberg carol tolan william j hume george h hume relatives william hume brother leslie p hume daughterinlaw jaquelin holliday jack hume  was an american businessman and conservative philanthropist he cofounded basic american foods the worlds largest producer of dried onion and garlic and dried potatoes used primarily for instant mashed potatoes he was a major donor to president ronald reagan and a patron of the arts contents  biography  early life  business career  philanthropy  personal life  death  legacy  references biographyedit early lifeedit jaquelin holliday hume was born in  in harbor point michigan he had a brother william hume he grew up in indianapolis indiana he graduated from princeton university in princeton new jersey in  where he had been a member of the charter club he then received an mba from the harvard business school in cambridge massachusetts in 0 business careeredit with his brother he cofounded the basic vegetable products company in  the company sold dried onion and garlic as well as dried beans after it successfully merged with its competitors it became the worlds largest producer of dried onion and garlic in the 0s he founded the american potato company it became the worlds largest producer of dried potato products including instant mash potatoes both companies later became known as basic american foods on december   he filed the patent named process of producing large dehydrated onion pieces us 0 a philanthropyedit he served as chairman of the board of trustees of the pacific presbyterian medical center he also served as chairman of the san francisco museum of art and vice chairman of the asian art foundation in  he established the jaquelin hume foundation seventeen years later in  he established the foundation for teaching economics a nonprofit organization which promotes the teaching of economics in elementary and high schools in the united states he received the george washington honor medal from the freedoms foundation near valley forge pennsylvania a conservative organization for his philanthropic work to promote free market economics he was a staunch supporter of and donor to ronald reagan both in his gubernatorial and presidential campaigns indeed he had known president reagan as earlier as  he was also a close friend of edwin meese who went on to serve as the th attorney general of the united states from  to  hume established citizens for america and the served on the board of the ronald reagan presidential foundation two organizations which promoted reagans ideas he also advised president reagan and helped him choose top advisors in his first cabinet a letter from president reagan to hume and his wife dated april   has been published in reagan a life in letters0 he also raised funds for other conservative republicans he served on the alumni council of his alma mater princeton university he received the alumni achievement award from his other alma mater the harvard business school in  he was a member of the pacificunion club a gentlemens club in san francisco california personal lifeedit he was married to caroline howard hume a philanthropist they had four children patricia highberg carol tolan william j hume and george h hume they resided in san francisco california deathedit he died of a cancerrelated stroke in san francisco on tuesday october   legacyedit the jacquelin h hume papers are kept at the hoover institution archives on the campus of stanford university in stanford california according to the abstract it contains correspondence memoranda reports studies lists and financial records relating to republican party fundraising activities especially in california election campaigns of ronald reagan especially his presidential campaign in  and the gubernatorial and presidential administrations of ronald reagan the jacqulin hume foundation remains an established conservative nonprofit organization since  it has focused on education reform in the united states especially charter schools vouchers standards and curricula it has granted donations to the center for education reform the state policy network the institute for justice the alliance for school choice and the association of american educators his son william j hume aka jerry hume serves as the chairman of basic american foods he is also a conservative philanthropist referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t bruce lambert jaquelin hume  dried fruit producer and philanthropist the new york times october 0   a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q food processing pioneer jack hume chicago tribune october 0   a b c d e f g h i j k l m jaquelin holliday hume  archived 000 at the wayback machine princeton alumni weekly january    a b harvard business school alumni achievement awards  a b c d basic american foods about us  google patents  a b c d justin torres jaquelin hume foundation a singleminded focus leads a small foundation to an outsized impact philanthropy march  april 00  a b c jaquelin hume orlando sentinel october 0   a b frances fitzgerald way out there in the blue reagan star wars and the end of the cold war new york city simon and schuster 00 p    kiron k skinner annelise anderson martin anderson reagan a life in letters new york city simon and schuster 00 p 0   the pacific union club constitution  bylaws published by the pacificunion club san francisco california may    a b online archive of california register of the jaquelin h hume papers  a b stanford university libraries jaquelin h hume papers  retrieved fro